 Hispanics, whose incidence of diabetes is two to three times as high as the population of the United States as a whole, can learn how to manage the illness at a free half-day clinic Saturday at St.
 Heredity and diet appear to be the major reasons that 14 to 21 percent of Hispanics -- and up to 40 percent in the 64 to 75 age group -- contract diabetes, said Rochelle McNamara, executive director of the Diabetes Society of Santa Clara Valley.
